TOTTENHAM Hotspur manager Antonio Conte praised ‘extraordinary’ Watford boss Claudio Ranieri ahead of today’s Premier League derby, revealing they are planning a New Year’s dinner between their families. The two Italian tacticians will face off on today at 4:00pm Nigerian time and it promises to be an intriguing match. During his Zoom press conference, Conte also answered some questions in Italian from Sky Sport Italia about the game and his admiration for veteran Ranieri. “First of all, there is great respect for the man. Claudio is a top person. There is friendship and shared admiration off the field too, between our respective families,” said Conte.   LEROY SANE: Bayern in-form strike force     EPL stars headline Africa Cup of Nations     DStv, Gotv to beam all AFCON action live   - Advertisement - Both of these Italian coaches have won the Premier League title, although Ranieri’s was historic at the helm of minnows Leicester City. “I think he achieved something extraordinary winning with Leicester, proving to everyone what kind of a coach he is. “In Italy, he worked at practically every big club other than Milan, so that says it all. He is a coach with experience, charisma and yet is always eager to challenge himself. “He accepted this latest challenge to come back to England. I am keeping my fingers crossed, because he beat me last season!”